parse.title: List of Commonwealth visits made by Elizabeth II

text.*:
Queen Elizabeth II became Head of the Commonwealth upon the death of her father, King George VI, on 6 February 1952. Since then, she has toured the Commonwealth of Nations and their territories and dependencies widely. She has visited all except Cameroon and Rwanda, two of the most recent members.

Tours of the British Islands are excluded from the list below.
